HEADWORD: Khutbah
<hw>Khut"bah</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.]</ety> <def>An
address or public prayer read from the steps of the pulpit in Muslim
mosques, offering glory to God, praising Mohammed and his descendants,
and the ruling princes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

